The U.S. government has been double-dealing on its "Taiwan independence" game but doubling down, especially since the beginning of this year. It has sold weapons to the region, allowed top officials to visit the island, and even once deleted "Taiwan is part of China" from its official website. The U.S. today just pays lip service to its proclaimed one-China policy. Editor: Yuan Xin Chief editor: Ge Jing (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)